Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.88,0:00:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nheaven
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.36,0:00:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The phenomena of paying attention\Nphenomena of paying attention is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.68,0:00:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,automatic\Nbecause the ego is feeding on data and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.55,0:01:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it's always looking for data\Nand that's a con that that's a quality
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.44,0:01:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ego. You don't claim credit for\Nyour heart beating all the time. You
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.92,0:01:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "Well, I'm making my heart beat."\NYou don't say that, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.24,0:01:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Take the same attitude towards mental\Nmental phenomena as you do towards
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.79,0:01:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,physical.\NRarely do you decide to do something
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.88,0:01:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,physically. You think you do it all the\Ntime. It's rare. It's so rare that when
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.43,0:01:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it happens, you notice it.\NThe phenomenon are happening
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.84,0:01:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,autonomously in this ego self that is\Ncalled I. What it does is constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.56,0:01:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,claim credit as author. It claims credit\Nof author. It's the author of your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.07,0:01:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,experience. It's who you think you are.\NSo that's the leading edge of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.52,0:01:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only way you can go beyond it is\Nto realize the presence of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.64,0:01:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with a capital S as the field in which\Nthis phenomena is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.04,0:02:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneously.\NYou stop looking at the event and you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.47,0:02:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,look at the field and you realize you\Nare the field
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.00,0:02:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and that this sense of a personal eye is\Na propensity that is arising in the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.59,0:02:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,field.\Nits degree of likelihood increases the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.08,0:02:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,lower the level of consciousness and\Ndecreases. So as consciousness evolves,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.20,0:02:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it begins to spontaneously intuit it and\Nsense
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.28,0:02:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is not its own mother and\Nfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.40,0:02:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There would have to be a mother and\Nfather of the mother and father. You see
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.87,0:02:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,by infinite regression you would say and\Nthen and then and then what and so how
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.56,0:02:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,does this sense of self even arise?\NEnlightenment is the dropping of a sense
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.87,0:03:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of personal self as the determiner of\Nbehaviors and decisions and who you are
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.31,0:03:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to see that you are the\Nfield.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.56,0:03:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The phenomena of the Olympics is a whole\Nenergy field is it not? People feel that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.12,0:03:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,certain sense the minute they turn the\NTV on to the because they picked up the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.20,0:03:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,field. There's no no performers there\Nyet, nothing happening, but they've
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.48,0:03:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,already picked up on the field. So you\Nbegin to instead of looking for
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.48,0:03:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,specifics,\Nyou look more for a generality,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.95,0:03:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to sense and begin to identify\Nwith the field with the field. And you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.87,0:03:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,realize that decisions\Nare made within the field and then the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.84,0:03:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,field influences the likelihood of the\Nphenomena happening uh within the linear
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.72,0:03:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,domain. The decision to be forgiving\Nincreases the likelihood of forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.48,0:04:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but it doesn't cause it.\NYou say when you get up this morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.04,0:04:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,dear God, help please help me to be\Nforgiving to myself and and and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.23,0:04:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone.\NThat doesn't mean you haven't just made
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.00,0:04:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it happen. You haven't determined it\Nhappen. All you've done is increased the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.23,0:04:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,likelihood of this event being\Nrecontextualized in such a way that you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.72,0:04:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,see there's nothing to forgive.\NEach thing is only being what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.16,0:04:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing is only being what it is,\Nincluding being wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.36,0:04:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego loves to be right.\NSo you see the seduction of being right
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.32,0:04:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see how the ego falls into it.\NSo what happens is you become too
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.16,0:04:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,sophisticated, too spiritually\Nsophisticated
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.47,0:04:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and irriodite\Nto fall for the ego anymore. I think
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.19,0:05:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what happens. You become so\Nsophisticated
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.63,0:05:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've learned its nature and you\Nthen refuse it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.63,0:05:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you get to the core of the ego,\Nas I've told you before,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.03,0:05:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you've surrendered all the illusions of\Ncausality and personal identity and all
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.00,0:05:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,these things.\NYou then exist in an infinite silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.03,0:05:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite silence. The\NAnd then the knowingness comes
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.16,0:05:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that the one thing you're hanging on to.\NYou you thought you've let go of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.32,0:05:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,everything.\NYou haven't let go of everything. You've
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.28,0:05:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,let go of life. You haven't let go of\Nlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.16,0:05:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You still think that you are the source\Nof your life. And without you being
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.68,0:06:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,watchful of it, your life will\Ndisappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.56,0:06:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The last great illusion experientially\Nthe experiential reality of this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.84,0:06:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,particular speaker was all had been\Nreleased. All had been surrendered.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.44,0:06:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There was only infinite\Npower and knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.31,0:06:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There came the temptation\Nto own the power.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.44,0:06:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All power is yours. Claim it.\NThat was the la the the luciferic
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.28,0:06:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,temptation came almost at the last\Nminute. Silent unspoken as a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.84,0:06:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,knowingness.\NAll power is yours. Claim it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.00,0:06:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not answerable to anyone. Karma,\Nyou're beyond karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.36,0:07:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are all illusions.\NIn the silence came the knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.16,0:07:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All power is yours. You can see how love\Nonce you surrender love, you could do
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.72,0:07:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,anything to anybody, couldn't you? It's\Nactually that innate love we have for
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.36,0:07:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,our fellow human being that makes us\Nhold back at the last moment
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.59,0:07:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,unless we're way below 200.\NAnd then when that was silenced, it was
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.44,0:07:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,as I say, it was like a high alpine\Nspace, very rarified.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.63,0:07:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hardly anybody had ever been there. You\Ncould see who'd been there and you could
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.44,0:07:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,see what they'd said by saying, "See, I\Nmean, knowing this, you felt the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.52,0:07:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of those who' been there." And uh so\Nwhat would a person want power for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.08,0:07:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be a drag, wouldn't it?\NI consider it a drag.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.19,0:07:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing worse than having power\Nover others. I mean, how would you like
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.40,0:08:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to have power over everybody? I mean,\Nyou just think of the karma of it on top
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.96,0:08:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of it.\NSo, power over others was practically
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.03,0:08:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the last thing. And when it disappeared,\Nthere remained only
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.80,0:08:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,only life itself.\NThe awareness arose.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.63,0:08:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The one thing you're clinging to is\Nlife. Life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.31,0:08:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego thinks that it is the author of\Nyour life. If it's the author of your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.84,0:08:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,thoughts, actions, and everything else,\Nit naturally thinks it's the author of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.76,0:08:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,your existence. So, the very core of the\Nego arose.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.76,0:08:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then came the knowingness to\Nsurrender life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.12,0:08:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I and then came a terror a terror.\NThe ego's existence is anchored in a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.48,0:08:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,profound\Nbelief system that has gone on for
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.16,0:09:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,millennia.\NAnd up came
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.83,0:09:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the eye as the core and essence and\Nsource of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.68,0:09:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This too, oh Lord, this too must be\Nlaid. And then with terror the dread
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.48,0:09:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,came up, the fear came up in droves,\Nmillennia of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.16,0:09:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And the knowingness, the frequency, the\Nvibration of the energy and the aura of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.36,0:09:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the enlightened being from whom I'd\Npicked it up in some lifetime came
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.12,0:09:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,through as a knowingness\Nthat all fear is illusion. All fear is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.76,0:09:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,illusion.\NAll fear is illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.00,0:09:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the trust in the absoluteness of\Nthat teaching comes from the power of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.68,0:09:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,certainty. And that's what a false\Nteacher cannot give you. It has to be
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.95,0:10:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of absolute certainty\Nthat you can lay down your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.48,0:10:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly the door to eternity opened up\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.20,0:10:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the terror went away. Huh? Then was the\Ninfinite stillness of the infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.48,0:10:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of all of of everythingness is\Ndivinity. So the divinity of all of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.39,0:10:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,creation shines forth\Nand you're unable to function for quite
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.00,0:10:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,a while.\NNow what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.60,0:10:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there is no personal self from\Nwhich to guide the functioning of the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.92,0:10:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,body. Even that is problematic. And it\Nwalks about spontaneously like a top.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.04,0:10:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Like you see it walk about like a top\Nright now. It walks around like a top.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.88,0:10:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It does what the heck it's going to do.\NI don't know anything to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.51,0:10:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How would I know what it's going to do?\NYou know what I'm saying? The
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.80,0:10:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,presumption that I know what it's going\Nto do and I'm determining what it's
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.60,0:11:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,going to do would reinforce the belief\Nthat I am the decider. That's the innate
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.76,0:11:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,portion of the ego. It's not only the\Ncreator of your life. It's the decider
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.24,0:11:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of your actions. And you see that the\Nego is the inner majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.16,0:11:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a majesty.\NMajesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.24,0:11:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you understand messianic narcissism.\NYou see these crazy rulers. I will kill
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.32,0:11:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,300 million. Saul.\NSome have killed 100 million. Saul. They
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.04,0:11:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,deserved it.\NThe death of a 100 million people means
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.51,0:11:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing. And when brought to court, they\Nstick out their tongue, drop their
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.00,0:11:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,pants, and show the rear to the judge\Nwho orders them out of court. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.72,0:11:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The value of these uh trials\Nis that you see the core of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.04,0:12:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,blatantly displayed for you. You say\Nthat's them. No, that's your ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.68,0:12:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Without love, you would also slaughter\N100 million people. The constraint is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.83,0:12:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,with love, you can't do it.\NThat's why the luciferic says, "Forget
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.16,0:12:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,love. It's just a limitation."\NI had a teacher actually tell me that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.72,0:12:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and he became Lucifer and he was\Ncalibrated high and he crashed very low.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.16,0:12:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is just an attachment.\NPersonal
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.72,0:12:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,love is an attachment.\NDivine love is a quality of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.95,0:12:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Quality of divinity. So when you\Nsurrender and release on a quality
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.48,0:12:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,invalidate a quality of divinity, you\Njust rejected
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.36,0:12:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,love as one of the innate qualities of\Ndivinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.12,0:12:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore he crashed. He crashed.\NHe crashed. and with them crash lava
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.95,0:13:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,students\Nsome of which run five or six pro a day
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.12,0:13:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a very important error not to\Nmake all love emanates from divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.76,0:13:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,what you want to transcend is attachment\NI can't live without
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.32,0:13:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,having that person controlling that\Nperson etc
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.80,0:13:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,so by becoming acquainted with the\Nnature of the ego you're in You begin to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.76,0:13:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically transcend it. Having heard\Nthese words, having heard these words,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.76,0:13:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you are already transcending the\Npersonal ego to a greater degree than
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.36,0:13:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you were. As we said, because it's in\Nthe field now, because it's in the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.00,0:13:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,field, you don't have to pay attention\Nto it all the time. It begins to move to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.24,0:13:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to work on its own. To have heard that\Nwithin the field with absolute certainty
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.20,0:13:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,already changes outcomes. Do you\Nunderstand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.00,0:14:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because the overall field then begins to\Ninfluence. So when you're trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.88,0:14:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,change a behavior, counting it every\Ntime that it occurs,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.19,0:14:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,even though you don't attempt to change\Nthe behavior, it's already changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.92,0:14:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already changing.\NJust the knowingness be, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.80,0:14:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,pervades one's aura and already you\Nbegin to experience the personal self
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.72,0:14:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,differently.\NFirst of all, you're not at the effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.39,0:14:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not the slave of it. It's not who\Nyou are. It's an option. It's an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.24,0:14:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, to feel that I am who I am is only\Nan option. Heck, I thought it was a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.88,0:14:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,certainty. I thought you're born with\Nit. You know, you come into the world
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.36,0:14:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and blubber and carry on like that.\NThat's the worst part of getting reborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.56,0:14:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I really wouldn't want to\Nfirst first 50 years are tough. I tell
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.80,0:15:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you life doesn't get better till you at\Nleast 50. I'll tell you how people get
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.48,0:15:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,through to 50 be compassion for mankind.\NSeeing what it takes to get there before
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.00,0:15:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the great heroes of wisdom start keeping\Nyou from putting your foot in the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.80,0:15:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,putting put your foot in the crank\Nagain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.95,0:15:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, so in the old days, the old model A\Nmodel T for it, it had a crank, you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.32,0:15:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,know, you crank it and you had to be\Ncareful because the kickback would break
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.24,0:15:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,your arm. So\Nyou learn to avoid the model T4s.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.72,0:15:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So wisdom\Nis wisdom accrs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.92,0:15:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Every spiritual\Nteacher you listen to, every book you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.51,0:15:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,read, every spiritual person you\Nencounter is already advancing your
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.76,0:15:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,field. It's advancing your field. They\Nsay hang out with holy company. It means
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.44,0:15:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that the field itself is supportive.\NThat's the charge you feel. For
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.48,0:16:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,instance, when you turn in on the\NOlympics, you're picking up the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.56,0:16:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Olympics. You know, you feel an\Nexcitement and a certain charge
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.36,0:16:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's nobody even on the screen\Nyet. It's just the announcer and now
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.07,0:16:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,tonight will resume and so and so and\Nalready you're feeling that surge of the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.51,0:16:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,sense of the energy. Just the same as\Nwhen you walk into one of the great
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.75,0:16:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,cathedrals in the world when you look in\Nthe pyramids of Eg in pyramids in Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.24,0:16:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I meditated in um most people meditate\Nin the first try to meditate in the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.63,0:16:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,first pyramid. There's too much traffic\Nin the first pyramid plus it smells bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.39,0:16:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a sarcophagus that people have\Npeed in for a thousand years. There's no
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.27,0:16:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,restroom, you know, and you hunt 400 ft\Nup through this thing. You aren't about
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.44,0:16:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to walk back out to go to the bathroom.\NSo, I'm sure there's some people that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.04,0:16:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know what, too?\NEgyptians are funny. It's, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.60,0:17:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,people write graffiti on on the wall and\Nthey just leave it. Anybody else want to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.36,0:17:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,erase it, you know, like remember it\Nsaid in Korean some guy's name 1937, the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.91,0:17:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Egyptians just leave it there.\NAnyway, you sense the the energy and the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.72,0:17:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,grandeur of all that exists uh despite\Nsuperficial existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.88,0:17:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You get the feeling of the sacrificial\Nenergy. the sacrificial energy. So those
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.48,0:17:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,who make sacrificial commitments etc to\Nfurther the evolution of their
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.20,0:17:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. I mean like a contender\Nin the Olympics certainly does make a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.96,0:17:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,commitment and you you you sense the\Nsacrificial core of it as well. I say
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.24,0:17:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,they all do it for God whether they're\Nconsciousness conscious of it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.91,0:18:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, how many fall to their\Nknees after their performance?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.72,0:18:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very heartwarming too, is it not?\NYou see, after their performance, they
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.67,0:18:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,cross themsel and you see great sports\Nfigures do that. Gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.36,0:18:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So one essence then is gratitude,\Nhumility
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.55,0:18:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to witness the sacredness of all that\Nexists.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.76,0:18:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To get a sense of the eye, who the real\Neye is and to realize that the real eye
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.96,0:18:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is the field, the entire field out of\Nwhich the sense of a personal eye
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.32,0:18:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,crystallizes.\NTo get a jump on the experiencer,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.16,0:18:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to be quick. It happens in one\N10,000th of a second. Within 110,000 of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.24,0:18:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a second,\Nthe sense of I has already claimed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.08,0:19:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,credit for moving the arm. It's already\Nclaimed credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.24,0:19:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It all the time believes that it is the\Nsource of its own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.67,0:19:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The core of the ego then\Nis we call egoomania
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.32,0:19:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,grandiosity.\NAnd the core of the ego is it that it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.40,0:19:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks it is God. It does think it is\NGod. It does. People say I don't believe
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.96,0:19:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that. I said who just said that?\NWho just decided to say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.12,0:19:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the core of the narcissistic ego\Nis God. Therefore, Nero and all the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.03,0:19:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,great egoomaniacs, iron, the terrible\NHenry VII, right down to the present
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.67,0:19:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,time, Alesovich,\Npeople on trial now, heads of certain
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.48,0:19:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,nations to tell the tell the whole world\Nto go to hell. They're just going to do
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.24,0:19:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,what they're going to do.\NHow can you speak rationally to that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.12,0:20:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which is coming out of such an\Nincredible egoomania?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.00,0:20:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you tell somebody who believes\Nthat he's God to be humble and deal with
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.24,0:20:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,other countries in an even-handed way?\NSounds nonsensical, does it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.72,0:20:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He goes home and says, "Boy, are they\Nidiots?" You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.72,0:20:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So\Nyou're way ahead of the game if you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.88,0:20:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,realize that the core of the ego is this\Negoomaniac
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.20,0:20:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that claims credit for all decisions,\Nall thoughts. It actually claims credit
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.40,0:20:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for your own existence.\NIt is because of I of I
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.64,0:20:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that you even exist.\NSo the fear comes up. If I surrender the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.76,0:20:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,source of life, then I will die.\NAnd you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.88,0:21:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You think you won't die, but you do. The\Nego self actually experiences death. In
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.64,0:21:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that instant, you realize it never\Nexperienced death ever. It left the body
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.36,0:21:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of whatever it was at the time from\Nsalamander to peacock
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.44,0:21:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to to a sailor or whatever you were. And\Nit never once accepted its own the the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.60,0:21:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,reality. It always made a certain\Npresumption
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.96,0:21:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond all time. Then the core of the\Nego is its refusal to accept God as the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.24,0:21:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,author of existence.\NIt will not accept that to the point of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.28,0:21:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,death. It will not accept it to the\Ndeath of all of its countrymen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.40,0:21:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Any one of those that you see will\Nwillingly slaughter their entire
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.52,0:21:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,country.\NThey will willingly slaughter all of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.36,0:21:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind.\NThey will willingly let loose a dirty
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.20,0:22:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,nuclear bomb just out of malevolence.\NAnd I scares me when I see people
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.40,0:22:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,tempting them to see how far they can go\Nbefore they do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.67,0:22:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll do it just for fun. They don't\Nneed an excuse. If there is no
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.48,0:22:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,conscience, then you wouldn't need\Nreason, would you? or an excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.20,0:22:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You would just do that because that's\Nyour right, sovereign right as God. So
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.24,0:22:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego's\Nproblem is its inability to admit that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.72,0:22:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it is not God.\NThat's the whole core of philosophic
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.32,0:22:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,relativism etc. is the illusion that it\Nis the core of the ego that is divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.28,0:22:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, that's why enlightenment is\Nso difficult to achieve because
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.28,0:22:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that which assumes it's in divin it is\Ndivinity
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.32,0:23:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,will not allow for any infringement.\NIt maintains its illusion of divinity no
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.79,0:23:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,matter all the confronting evidence. All\Nthe confronting evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.24,0:23:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It has contempt for confronting\Nevidence. Ignorance has certain forms of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.55,0:23:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,ignorance have contempt for wisdom, have\Ncontempt for
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.67,0:23:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,uh age, have contempt for truth. A great\Ndeal of the world has contempt for
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.28,0:23:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,truth. Contempt. They'll go out to\Nforeign countries and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.76,0:23:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and heap contempt against their own\Ncountry, their own countrymen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.79,0:23:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Raise their man with souls who dead who\Nhimself has not said. This is my own my
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.08,0:23:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,native land. They're out there. You can\Nsee them on television with soul so dead
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.72,0:23:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrating\Nthe bottom. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.64,0:23:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego therefore will not stop at\Nanything. You can't count the common
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.60,0:24:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,sense and the ego will stop an asalent.\NYou cannot at all depend on that. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.24,0:24:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,suicidal. Oh, at the last minute he will\Nsee the fallacy and the foolishness of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.32,0:24:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,setting off,\Nyou know, destroying all of Europe or
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.72,0:24:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,something.\NDon't count on it. In fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.27,0:24:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that makes it more fun than anything. If\Nyou can wipe out all of Europe at the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.76,0:24:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,same time, the better.\NThat's the human ego. So, we see if you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.91,0:24:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,can see it out there, that's because\Nit's already within you or you couldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.08,0:24:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,see it out there.\NThe core of the ego then doesn't care of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.48,0:24:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,anything at all about you. It's out to\Ndestroy you so long as it can maintain
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.44,0:24:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,its sense of sovereignty.\NRadical reality then means the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.08,0:24:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,willingness to surrender the claim to\Nsovereignty
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.72,0:25:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of the inner sense of a personal eye and\Nsurrender to the field. Then ego says if
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.08,0:25:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you surrender me to the field you'll\Nbecome nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.32,0:25:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is if you surrender me to the\Nfield, you become everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.24,0:25:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You become all of it because all of it\Nand what you are are identical. The
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.64,0:25:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,sense of self,\Nwhat would I do without her? I wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.48,0:25:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,get through tomorrow night, I'll tell\Nyou.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.44,0:25:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. What about this reality? Okay.\NIf you haven't eaten in a couple of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.64,0:25:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,days, she complains. Yeah.\NThursday. Last day. Mon Monday. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.79,0:25:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's see. Uh we will stop and then\Nwe will resume at what time?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.67,0:26:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> 2 o'clock.\N>> We will stop. We will then resume at 2
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.96,0:26:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,o'clock.\NThat was really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.64,0:26:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah,\N>> it was superb. It was wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.96,0:26:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Uh Gail, are you going to talk first?\N>> Go ahead. Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.84,0:26:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Good afternoon.\NGlad you're all just want to uh make an
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.12,0:26:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,announcement that in March in the second\NWednesday of March we're meeting here
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.44,0:26:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and not where we did before um in terms\Nof having a question and answer
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.52,0:26:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,um discussion. So if you want more\Ninformation on that go to the website or
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.24,0:26:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,call the center but it's not at the\NEpiscopal Church. It's here at this um
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.67,0:27:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,center. There's something else I'm\Nsupposed to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.76,0:27:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll come back.\N>> What' you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.03,0:27:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,>> The rest of the schedule. Oh, I'm sorry.\NThe rest of the schedule is doctor's
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.55,0:27:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,going to lecture, Nico is going to\Nchant, and then we're going to have our
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.27,0:27:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,final break. Okay. Thanks.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.03,0:27:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, the problem was we overloaded St.\NAndrews. We didn't know such a crowd was
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.88,0:27:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,going to come. I originally told them\Nabout 60 70 people. I figured, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.20,0:27:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,people around Sedona, maybe a few from\NPhoenix. Oh. So, we decided we better
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.76,0:27:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,move back here, you know, and Nancy was\Nvery gracious and made the arrangement
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.64,0:27:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for us. So, the dates are the same. It's\Njust the location is different. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.44,0:27:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I said the second Wednesday. Someone\Njust told me it's the third Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.32,0:27:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> It is the third Wednesday. This\Nand then after this
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.84,0:27:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,next in March, it will be the third\NWednesday. March it'll be different but
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.67,0:28:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,after that it's the same just the\Nlocation is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.48,0:28:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> However it happens is however it\Nhappens.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.24,0:28:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad that everything's happening\Nspontaneously. I wouldn't want to take
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.36,0:28:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,responsibility for it.\NThe awareness that everything is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.12,0:28:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,happening spontaneously gives you a very\Nrapid leap forward in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.15,0:28:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You become aware that all phenomena are\Noccurring as a consequence of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.24,0:28:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,not as a consequence of a personal eye.\NFor instance, who speaks when the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.27,0:28:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual speech teacher speaks? Who's\Nspeaking? If not the personal eye, I
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.96,0:29:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want anything to do with it.\NIt's happening of its own. Classically,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.84,0:29:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that's called the perushia. The presence\Nwithin speaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.08,0:29:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So you become you become progressively\Naware
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.72,0:29:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's the field and not a personal\Nself that uh and then phenomena are a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.44,0:29:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of the field and of course\Npart of the field is intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.96,0:29:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So that intention increases the\Nlikelihood of certain responses
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.27,0:29:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and but the responses themselves are\Nstill autonomous, spontaneous, occurring
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.55,0:29:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of their own. The fulfillment of a\Npotential becoming an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.91,0:29:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of intention.\NThe Heisenberg principle. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.08,0:30:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,core to this commitment is devotion to\Nit. Devotion because that energizes the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.48,0:30:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,power that you that you need because\Nyou're overcoming, you know, really
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.32,0:30:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,millennia of limitation of the ego. As\Nyou see, it developed over great
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.39,0:30:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,expanses of time. The ego didn't just\Narise uh with man. It pre-existed as a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.36,0:30:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as a quality of life, quality of life\Nitself and then its manifestation
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.44,0:30:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,uh gradually took us away from the\Nawareness of its source. And so to seek
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.88,0:30:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment is to seek to return to\Nthe source.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.55,0:30:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that the experiencer wants to\Njump ahead at the peak of the prow of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.60,0:30:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the ship. you might say of the ego and\Ntake credit for everything that happens
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.76,0:31:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to get ahead of it takes it happens in\None 10,000th of a second. So you can't
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.32,0:31:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,valitionally jump it by 110,000 of a\Nsecond because your mind that's trying
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.08,0:31:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to jump to 10,000 of a second is is\Nitself moving at 10,000 of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.84,0:31:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'd be like a dog trying to catch\Nits tail. So you can't do it by specific
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.67,0:31:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,logical intention.\NYou do it by by becoming the field. So
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.72,0:31:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we say\Nto dedicate your life so that your life
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.24,0:31:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes the prayer.\NWho you are becomes the prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.79,0:31:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then\Nthe consequences of that is that one day
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.96,0:31:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,while you're walking through the woods\Nthinking about nothing, you become the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.39,0:31:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,field.\NYeah, it's worth the field. How did you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.48,0:31:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,fail to notice it? Huh? It's because\Nyou're you were focused in such a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.12,0:32:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,limited parameter of the linear\Ndimension. you see together with you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.88,0:32:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,know the belief in cause and effect.\NSo you become then the field in which
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.55,0:32:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,these phenomena\Num become self-revealing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.15,0:32:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How to discern\Nthe linear from the nonlinear is you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.96,0:32:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,realize that your reality is the\Nnonlinear and your expression your
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.51,0:32:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,expression is in the linear but your\Nsource your essence that which you are
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.55,0:32:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is nonlinear.\NUhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.27,0:32:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThe core then is the dedication.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.20,0:32:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the heart is more powerful than the\Nmind. See?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.08,0:32:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, devotion to truth, devotion\Nto spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.15,0:33:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is very powerful. The intellect alone\Ncan't do it. Otherwise, you could become
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.88,0:33:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightened by reading a lot of books.\NYou take a test on it, you get a 100
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.03,0:33:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,year length.\NWilly-nilly devotion also is not
