Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.83,0:37:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh it gives you a sense of where\Neverything is at. Now, this is not a a
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.96,0:37:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,way of valuing people, saying this\Nperson's worth more than this. Uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.11,0:37:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not true because somebody at 350\Ncan say a thing, you get it. And of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.00,0:37:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,course, it's been said for centuries by\Nsomebody at 800, but at 800, it doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.24,0:37:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,make any sense. So,\NI always tell people, first digest the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.44,0:37:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,easy ones before you try moving on.\NBefore you try moving on. And we pointed
