Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.96,0:40:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,experience of the presence of divinity\Nas infinite love.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.64,0:40:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore at a later life going back\Ninto the void
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.16,0:40:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowingness was that that quality\Nwas missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.04,0:41:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So that quality of divinity of infinite\Nlove was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.96,0:41:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, there was a decision to back\Nout of the void, which was not easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.44,0:41:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In as much as there's nothing there to\Nback out from or with
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.88,0:41:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a float did there was a thought that\Nfloated a pass past and I grabbed the I
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.48,0:41:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,grabbed the thought and expanded on it\Nand focused on it. It took hours of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.96,0:41:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,focus and concentration\Nand then I backed out. I backed out of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.28,0:41:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the void.\Nlater
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.59,0:41:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,went past the void. All right. But Hang\NPo never wrote anything about that. So
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.83,0:41:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the warning on Hang Poe because\Nhe's a very esteemed Zen master
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.11,0:41:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is that he then later went to 960\Nor 980 or something like that. 960
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.11,0:41:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that's where he went.\NBut that was after he wrote the book. So
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.48,0:42:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the book just negating the linear will\Ntake you to voidness but it won't take
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.11,0:42:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you to full realization. Huh? So we\Nmentioned that before because it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.07,0:42:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,frequent error. Once in a while I get a\Nletter uh in fact I got a letter this
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.72,0:42:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,year about somebody who had done the\Nvery thing the path of indigation landed
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.56,0:42:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in the nothingness of the void wanted to\Nknow if that's where we should be. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.96,0:42:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And Lisa I got to meet too.\NSo anyway, some of these people you get
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.24,0:42:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to meet in your present life and there\Nare famous names and we rever all of
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.24,0:42:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,them because each one contributes\Nsomething unique. Mother Teresa demon,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.76,0:42:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, demonstrated\Nand was and something unique about that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.52,0:42:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,particular level that she was at. And\NVivikananda, each of these people
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.24,0:42:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,contributed a very\Neach one has a unique piece of the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.11,0:42:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,overall picture.\NAny one of them can ring true with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.59,0:43:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So they say what teacher is the best?\Nthe one that you feel attracted to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.16,0:43:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,intuitively\Nattuned. Uh so we'll move to the next
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.35,0:43:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,one. Yes.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.20,0:43:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we said that every positionality is uh\Nheld in place by two things. There's an
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.52,0:43:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,attraction and there's also an aversion.\NSo all the levels of consciousness in
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.20,0:43:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the book transcending levels of\Nconsciousness. Uh each level you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.44,0:43:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,has an attraction and it has an\Naversion. Now these are just the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.16,0:43:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,dualities of attraction and aversion but\Nyou can see how they could apply to any
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.04,0:43:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness. We're attracted\Nto that which is familiar. Uh and we
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.83,0:43:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,have an aversion to changing. Uh we like\Nthe comfort of the familiar. We like
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.92,0:43:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,things that are easy and we feel that\Nthe change is going to take effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.72,0:44:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh we may feel pride that uh we we know\Nwhat we need to know whereas humility is
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.96,0:44:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't know much of anything.\NThe feeling of anger is a false sense of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.31,0:44:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,strength and the dread is to be to\Nappear weak and passivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.88,0:44:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh so this is puffing yourself up with\Nanger and you see that in international
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.16,0:44:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,politics.\NThis is the drivenness to win to gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.48,0:44:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the\Nleading edge of the ego which is always
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.68,0:44:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for gain for gain. Therefore you\Ndon't want a spiritual teacher who's
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.72,0:44:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for gain. Says we're focusing on\Nthroughout the teachers a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.80,0:44:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,again today.\NThe teacher has nothing to gain. Nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.96,0:44:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to gain. They're not interested in\Nsigning up followers, selling books, uh
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.48,0:44:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,multi-level merchandising,\Nsigning up people,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.72,0:45:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,selling them courses. There's no there's\Nno pitch to it. So that which has a
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.35,0:45:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,pitch has an ulterior motive. Yeah. Uh\Nso the attraction is to have money and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.68,0:45:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the aversion is poverty. Why? Because\Nthey think uh these things will bring
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.83,0:45:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you happiness. and these things will\Nnot. So the the cling is to the illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.83,0:45:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of what will bring you happiness. You'll\Nbe happy if you can control everything
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.11,0:45:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and the aversion is to accept things the\Nway they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.59,0:45:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThe attraction is the egotism that
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.59,0:45:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to save the world instead\Nof surrendering it to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.68,0:45:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So these are all emotional\Npayoffs and you can see that the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.92,0:45:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,attachment is to the emotional payoff.\NThe attachment is not to the thing
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.04,0:45:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,itself\Nbut the juice you get out of the thing
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.04,0:45:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,itself. To feel important gives you\Njuice. To feel you're right and that
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.88,0:46:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you're winning gives you juice. It isn't\Nthe winning. It isn't the being right.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.76,0:46:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're addicted to is the juice. So\Nthe ego is addicted to the juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.68,0:46:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you only have to surrender your\Nattachment to one thing, not all these
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.00,0:46:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,hundreds of things. The juice, no matter\Nwhat it is, it's the juice of the thing
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.28,0:46:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and not the thing itself.\NSo you only have to let go of your
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.59,0:46:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,attachment\Nuh to the juice of the ego's payoffs,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.88,0:46:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,whether they're anger, winning, being\Nbetter than, they're all the same. They
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.24,0:46:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,give you a certain feeling, and it's\Nthat high that you're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.48,0:46:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're looking for the high.\NThat's what drives the gambler back to
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.80,0:46:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the casino. You're looking for the high.\NThe person with his sexual addiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.80,0:46:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the high of a new conquest, you\Nknow.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.64,0:46:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's the little high that you get\Nout of these positions. Being right.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.44,0:47:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's boring being right. More fun\Nto be wrong. Why? Because they feel so
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.64,0:47:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,good.\NIt's easy to make somebody feel good.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.56,0:47:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Just let them win and be right up\Nuntil they catch on to what you're up
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.28,0:47:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to.\NWe all want to be fashionable, be right,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.80,0:47:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,be superior, be famous, be famous. So,\Nyou don't want a teacher that wants
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.07,0:47:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,anything these things. Being famous, uh,\Nbeing superior, being right. save the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.31,0:47:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,world.\NUh all right. The attraction is here to
